message.content:
A motorcycle is a two-wheeled vehicle powered by a gasoline engine. 
It has a set of handlebars for steering and a seat for the rider. 
The body of a motorcycle is typically made of metal and painted in various colors. 
The seat and handlebars of a motorcycle may be padded for comfort. 
Motorcycles come in a variety of shapes and sizes, from sporty to cruiser. 
They are often used for recreational purposes or for transportation on the roads. 
Motorcycles are found all around the world, particularly in urban areas.
